HEADWORD: Unbed
<hw>Un*bed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>bed</ets>.]</ety> <def>To raise or rouse from
bed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Eels <qex>unbed</qex> themselves and stir at the noise of
thunder.</q> <rj><qau>Walton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbedinned</ent>⟦br⟧
